Cell cycle

# A list of cell cycle markers, from Tirosh et al, 2015, is loaded with Seurat.  We can
# segregate this list into markers of G2/M phase and markers of S phase
s.genes <- tolower(cc.genes$s.genes)
g2m.genes <- tolower(cc.genes$g2m.genes)

seu <- CellCycleScoring(seu, s.features = s.genes, g2m.features = g2m.genes, set.ident = TRUE)
## Warning: The following features are not present in the object: ung, cdca7,
## mlf1ip, clspn, not searching for symbol synonyms
## Warning: The following features are not present in the object: hmgb2, birc5,
## tmpo, fam64a, ckap2, kif20b, hjurp, cdca3, hn1, cdc25c, rangap1, cdca2, psrc1,
## cenpa, not searching for symbol synonyms
DimPlot(seu,  reduction  = 'tsne')

Annotation

# Make a set of data.frames to keep track during cluster assignment.
clusters <- length(unique(seu$seurat_clusters))
cluster.assignments <- data.frame(
  cluster=(1:clusters)-1,
  name=rep(NA, clusters),
  row.names=(1:clusters)-1
)

cluster.assignments["13","name"] <- "NPB_nohox"
cluster.assignments["15","name"] <- "NPB_nohox_cycling"
cluster.assignments["18","name"] <- "NPB_hox2" #??
cluster.assignments["14","name"] <- "NPB_hox3" #??

cluster.assignments["11","name"] <- "dNC_nohox_cycling" # delaminating NC
cluster.assignments["0","name"] <- "dNC_nohox"
cluster.assignments["10","name"] <- "dNC_hoxa2b"
cluster.assignments["21","name"] <- "dNC_hox34" 
cluster.assignments["20","name"] <- "NC_trunk"

cluster.assignments["22","name"] <- "mNC_vagal"
cluster.assignments["8","name"] <- "mNC_hox34"

cluster.assignments["1","name"] <- "mNC_nohox" # migratory NC
cluster.assignments["2","name"] <- "mNC_arch1"
cluster.assignments["6","name"] <- "mNC_arch2"
cluster.assignments["5","name"] <- "mNC_head_mesenchymal"

cluster.assignments["3","name"] <- "Pigment_sox6_high"

seu$cell_type <- NA
seu$cell_type <- cluster.assignments$name[match(seu$seurat_clusters, cluster.assignments$cluster)]
# seu$cell_type <- paste0(seu$seurat_clusters, ":", seu$cell_type)
# seu$cell_type <- factor(seu$cell_type, paste0(cluster.assignments$cluster, ":", cluster.assignments$name))
# 
col.ls2 <- col.ls
# names(col.ls2) <- paste0(cluster.assignments$cluster, ":", cluster.assignments$name)
DimPlot(seu, label = T, group.by = "cell_type",
        reduction = "tsne", cols = alpha(col.ls2, 0.1), pt.size = 1,
        repel = T)

other markers: BMP11/gdf1

gdf11: cardiac and skeletal muscle https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5833306/

gdf11 is bmp11: https://www.oncotarget.com/article/20258/text/; https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3773925/

cadm1a: Predicted to be active in neuron projection; plasma membrane; and synapse

FeaturePlot(seu, features = c("cadm1a","gdf11"), pt.size = 0.1, reduction = "tsne")

ebf3a: sensory system

DotPlot(seu, features = c("gdf11","sema3d","ebf3a","meis2a","cadm1a","eya1","runx1","sox10"), group.by = "cell_type")

Vagal markers

itga3 is a heart marker ? https://etheses.whiterose.ac.uk/27656/1/DERRICK_Thesis_Aug2020.pdf

runx2b is a osteoblast lineage marker https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-021-27594-w

cxcl12a stromal branch

hyal4 cartilage, bone, periosteum, and tendon and ligament

fgf10a/b+ branch connected to gill pillar, tunica media, and perivascular cells, as well as a distinct type of gill cartilage
